description:
Description of the project 
 &nbsp; 
 Inflammation-induced intestinal barrier dysfunction is a key feature of several gastrointestinal disorders. Bovine whey contains bioactive components with potential barrier-protective and immunomodulatory properties, although its activity may depend on fraction composition. In this study, the effects of whole bovine whey (BWW) and skimmed bovine whey (BSW) were evaluated in a differentiated Caco-2/TC7:HT29-MTX co-culture model exposed to basolateral TNF-&alpha; + IFN-&gamma; (50 ng/mL, 24 h). Cytokine treatment significantly reduced transepithelial electrical resistance (TEER), downregulated CLDN1 and CLDN3, increased IL-1&beta; expression, and decreased MUC2 expression, whereas FITC-dextran permeability remained unchanged. Both whey fractions restored TEER to values comparable to control and also increased TEER under basal conditions. BWW attenuated cytokine-induced IL-1&beta; upregulation, whereas BSW increased MUC2 expression under both basal and inflammatory conditions. These results indicate that BWW and BSW improve epithelial barrier function under inflammatory conditions through distinct functional activities. 
 &nbsp; 
 Description of the dataset 
 &nbsp; 
 This dataset contains the experimental data associated with Figures S2 and 1-4 of the mentioned article. 
 &nbsp; 
 &nbsp; 
 Files included 
 -Raw Data Figure-S2.xlsx :Raw data regarding TEER values for figure S2. 
 -Raw Data Figure-1.xlsx : Raw data regarding TEER values for figure 1. 
 -Raw Data Figure-2.xlsx : Raw data regarding FITC-dextran flux values for figure 2. 
 -Raw Data Figure-3.xlsx : Raw data regarding qPCR values for figure 3. 
 -Raw Data Figure-4.xlsx : Raw data regarding qPCR values for figure 4. 
 &nbsp; 
 -Processed Data Figure-S2.xlsx :Processed data regarding TEER values for figure S2. 
 -Processed Data Figure-1.xlsx : Processed data regarding TEER values for figure 1. 
 -Processed Data Figure-2.xlsx : Processed data regarding FITC-dextran flux values for figure 2. 
 -Processed Data Figure-3.xlsx : Processed data regarding qPCR values for figure 3. 
 -Processed Data Figure-4.xlsx : Processed data regarding qPCR values for figure 4. 
 &nbsp; 
